The paper discusses machine learning methods for natural language processing and dialogue agents, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Memory Networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning, further supporting the likelihood of cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) as a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of comprehension via question answering, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) as well as natural language processing.
